<h1>Instance Variables</h1>
<p>Instance variables are often data we want to capture, like fields on the form. It's a "has-a" relationship with the class. In our case, a User has a name, email, and password. There are more information a user has, but for our systems, this is all we need.</p>
<p>The way to declare an instance variable is very similar to a variable  without a value. The only difference is that it usually have an accessor. The accessor is usually private, which means no one outside of this class can access this field.</p>
<img src="/images/instance_variables.png" width="400px">

<p>Here are a few more fields as an example:</p>
<pre><code class="java">public class User {
  private String name;
  private String email;
  private String password;

  private int age;
  private boolean vip = false;
}</code></pre>

